var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"location":"#TerrariaWiringHelper.jl","page":"TerrariaWiringHelper.jl","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.jl","text":"Documentation for TerrariaWiringHelper.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"docstrings/#Docstrings","page":"Docstrings","title":"Docstrings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.AndGate","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.AndGate","text":"(AndGate|XorGate){T<:Integer, V<:AbstractVector{<:Integer}}(gatestate::Bool, args::T, lampstates::V) <:AbstractGate\nCombGate{T, V} = Union{AndGate{T, V}, XorGate{T, V}}\n\nCombinatory gates in Terraria. gatestate tells the default (when all inputs are zero) state of the gate. args tells the number of inputs. lampstates lists how the inputs are wired to each logic lamp. \n\nExample\n\nConsider AndGate(false, 4, [0x12, 0x09, 0x04]). It's an AND gate whose default state is OFF. Since there are 4 args (named a-d), we consider the last 5 bits of each entry of lampstates. The leading bit tells the default state of the lamps. The other 4 bits (from lower to higher) tell which args are wired to the lamp. i.e.,\n\n0x12 = 0b10010 means the default state of the first lamp is ON and only b is connected to the lamp.\n0x09 = 0b01001 means the default state of the second lamp is OFF and a and d are connected to the lamp.\n0x04 = 0b00100 means the default state of the third lamp is OFF and only c is connected to the lamp.\n\njulia> AndGate(false, 4, [0x12, 0x09, 0x04])\n&(~b, ad, c)\n\nThe output is visualized via gate2string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.CombGate","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.CombGate","text":"(AndGate|XorGate){T<:Integer, V<:AbstractVector{<:Integer}}(gatestate::Bool, args::T, lampstates::V) <:AbstractGate\nCombGate{T, V} = Union{AndGate{T, V}, XorGate{T, V}}\n\nCombinatory gates in Terraria. gatestate tells the default (when all inputs are zero) state of the gate. args tells the number of inputs. lampstates lists how the inputs are wired to each logic lamp. \n\nExample\n\nConsider AndGate(false, 4, [0x12, 0x09, 0x04]). It's an AND gate whose default state is OFF. Since there are 4 args (named a-d), we consider the last 5 bits of each entry of lampstates. The leading bit tells the default state of the lamps. The other 4 bits (from lower to higher) tell which args are wired to the lamp. i.e.,\n\n0x12 = 0b10010 means the default state of the first lamp is ON and only b is connected to the lamp.\n0x09 = 0b01001 means the default state of the second lamp is OFF and a and d are connected to the lamp.\n0x04 = 0b00100 means the default state of the third lamp is OFF and only c is connected to the lamp.\n\njulia> AndGate(false, 4, [0x12, 0x09, 0x04])\n&(~b, ad, c)\n\nThe output is visualized via gate2string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.XorGate","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.XorGate","text":"(AndGate|XorGate){T<:Integer, V<:AbstractVector{<:Integer}}(gatestate::Bool, args::T, lampstates::V) <:AbstractGate\nCombGate{T, V} = Union{AndGate{T, V}, XorGate{T, V}}\n\nCombinatory gates in Terraria. gatestate tells the default (when all inputs are zero) state of the gate. args tells the number of inputs. lampstates lists how the inputs are wired to each logic lamp. \n\nExample\n\nConsider AndGate(false, 4, [0x12, 0x09, 0x04]). It's an AND gate whose default state is OFF. Since there are 4 args (named a-d), we consider the last 5 bits of each entry of lampstates. The leading bit tells the default state of the lamps. The other 4 bits (from lower to higher) tell which args are wired to the lamp. i.e.,\n\n0x12 = 0b10010 means the default state of the first lamp is ON and only b is connected to the lamp.\n0x09 = 0b01001 means the default state of the second lamp is OFF and a and d are connected to the lamp.\n0x04 = 0b00100 means the default state of the third lamp is OFF and only c is connected to the lamp.\n\njulia> AndGate(false, 4, [0x12, 0x09, 0x04])\n&(~b, ad, c)\n\nThe output is visualized via gate2string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.Z2ColMat","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.Z2ColMat","text":"Z2ColMat{C<:Integer, R<:Integer}(data::Vector{C}, size::Int)\nZ2ColMat(undef, m, n)\nZ2ColMat(::AbstractMatrix)\n\nmathbbZ_2 matrix stored in a Vector where each entry represents a column. size specifies the height. C and R are used for dispatch; they specify the integer type used to represent a column vector and a row vector respectively. See also bit2type, Z2RowMat\n\nExample\n\njulia> Z2ColMat([1, 3, 5], 3)\n3×3 Z2ColMat{UInt8, UInt8}:\n 1  1  1\n 0  1  0\n 0  0  1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.Z2RowMat","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.Z2RowMat","text":"Z2RowMat{C<:Integer, R<:Integer}(data::Vector{R}, size::Int)\nZ2RowMat(undef, m, n)\nZ2RowMat(::AbstractMatrix)\n\nmathbbZ_2 matrix stored in a Vector where each entry represents a row. size specifies the width. C and R are used for dispatch; they specify the integer type used to represent a column vector and a row vector respectively. See also bit2type, Z2ColMat\n\nExample\n\njulia> Z2RowMat([1, 3, 5], 3)\n3×3 Z2RowMat{UInt8, UInt8}:\n 1  0  0\n 1  1  0\n 1  0  1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.Z2Vector","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.Z2Vector","text":"Z2Vector{T<:Integer}(data::T, size::Int)\nZ2Vector(::AbstractVector)\n\nmathbbZ_2 vector stored in an integer data where each bit represents an entry. size specifies the length.\n\nExample\n\njulia> Z2Vector(0b10110, 5)\n5-element Z2Vector{UInt8}:\n 0\n 1\n 1\n 0\n 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.CombLogic-Tuple{Integer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{Bool}}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.CombLogic","text":"CombLogic(lamps, inputs, outputs::AbstractVector{Bool})\n\nReturn the lists of possible combinatory logics for given inputs and outputs.\n\nArguments\n\nlamps::Integer: the number of logic lamps on the gate, from 2 to 7.\ninputs::AbstractVector{<:Integer}: the list of input values specified by the lower bits of entries, with a 1 in front of the first bit.\noutputs::AbstractVector{Bool}: the expected return values of the logic. This should have the same length as inputs, although it's not strictly checked.\n\nExample\n\nImagine we want to check if a 4-bit input can be divided by 3. Further, the input is expected to have only one decimal digit, i.e. in 0:9. We don't care how the logic behaves for inputs 10:15. The truth table would be\n\nin out  in out\n0000 true  0101 false\n0001 false  0110 true\n0010 false  0111 false\n0011 true  1000 false\n0100 false  1001 true\n\nNow we try to find a configuration with least lamps.\n\njulia> inputs = 16:25; # `0:9` with the 5th last bit set to `1`\n\njulia> outputs = [true, false, false, true, false, false, true, false, false, true];\n\njulia> CombLogic(2, inputs, outputs) # there is no 2-lamp logic\nUnion{AndGate{Int64, StaticArraysCore.SVector{2, UInt8}}, XorGate{Int64, StaticArraysCore.SVector{2, UInt8}}}[]\n\njulia> CombLogic(3, inputs, outputs) # there are 12 3-lamp logics, all of which use XOR gates\n12-element Vector{Union{AndGate{Int64, StaticArraysCore.SVector{3, UInt8}}, XorGate{Int64, StaticArraysCore.SVector{3, UInt8}}}}:\n ^(~b, ad, c)\n ^(~b, abd, bc)\n ^(~ac, ad, ab)\n ^(~ac, abd, a)\n ^(~ac, cd, bc)\n ^(~ac, bcd, c)\n ^(~bd, c, a)\n ^(~bd, bc, ab)\n ^(~bd, cd, ad)\n ^(~bd, bcd, abd)\n ^(~acd, bc, c)\n ^(~acd, abd, ad)\n\nSee also CombGate\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.bit2type-Tuple{Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.bit2type","text":"bit2type(n::Integer) :: DataType\n\nReturns minimal integer type that contains n bits\n\nExamples\n\njulia> bit2type(5)\nUInt8\n\njulia> bit2type(9)\nUInt16\n\njulia> bit2type(32)\nUInt32\n\njulia> bit2type(33)\nUInt64\n\njulia> bit2type(100)\nUInt128\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.datamask-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Type{T}, Integer}} where T","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.datamask","text":"datamask(::Type{T}, size::Integer)\ndatamask(A::Z2Vector{T}) = datamask(T, A.size)\n\nInternal. Returns the bitmask of type T where the lower size bits are set to 1.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> datamask(UInt8, 3)\n0x07\n\njulia> datamask(Z2Vector(0b10110, 5))\n0x1f\n\njulia> datamask(Z2Vector(0b10110, 4))\n0x0f\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.fuse-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.fuse","text":"fuse(setup::Integer, input::Integer) = fuse(setup & input)\n\nReturn the state of a tile connected to multiple wires. Each bit of setup represents the state of a wire, and each bit of input represents the connection of a wire to the tile.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.fuse-Tuple{Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.fuse","text":"fuse(input::Integer)\n\nReturn the state of a tile connected to multiple wires. Each bit of the input represents the state of a wire.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> TerrariaWiringHelper.fuse(0b0110)\nfalse\n\njulia> TerrariaWiringHelper.fuse(0b1011)\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.gate2string-Tuple{CombGate}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.gate2string","text":"gate2string(G::CombGate)\n\nConvert a CombGate into a readable string. See also CombGate, lampstate2string, logicsymb.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.getbit-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.getbit","text":"getbit(x::Integer, n::Integer)\n\nGet the n-th (counting from zero) last bit of x. See also setbit\n\nExample\n\njulia> [getbit(0b10110, n) for n in 0:4]\n5-element Vector{Bool}:\n 0\n 1\n 1\n 0\n 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.hasallcolor-Tuple{TerrariaWiringHelper.AbstractGate, Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.hasallcolor","text":"hasallcolor(G::AbstractGate, mask::Integer)\nhasallcolor(mask::Integer) = Fix2(hasallcolor, mask)\n\nCheck if some gate is connect to some wires.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.hascolor-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.hascolor","text":"hascolor(lampstate::Integer, mask::Integer) = lampstate & mask\nhascolor(mask::Integer) = Fix2(hascolor, mask)\nhascolor(G::AbstractGate, mask::Integer) = any(hascolor(mask), lampstates(G))\n\nCheck if some lamp is connected to some wire (combination), or if some gate has a such lamp.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.lampstate2string-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.lampstate2string","text":"lampstate2string(lampstate::Integer, args::Integer)\n\nConvert binary coded lampstate into a readable string. args tells the number of distinct inputs.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> lampstate2string(0b1111, 4)\n\"abcd\"\n\njulia> lampstate2string(0b11101, 4)\n\"~acd\"\n\njulia> lampstate2string(0b10000, 4)\n\"~\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.logicsymb-Tuple{typeof(TerrariaWiringHelper.AND)}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.logicsymb","text":"logicsymb(::typeof(AND|XOR)|::CombGate)\n\nReturn '&' or '^' according to input.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.setbit-Tuple{Integer, Bool, Integer}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.setbit","text":"setbit(x::Integer, y::Bool, n::Integer)\n\nSet the n-th (counting from zero) last bit of x to y. See also getbit.\n\nExample\n\njulia> string(setbit(0b10110, true, 0), base = 2)\n\"10111\"\n\njulia> string(setbit(0b10110, false, 0), base = 2)\n\"10110\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.type2bit-Union{Tuple{Type{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T<:Integer","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.type2bit","text":"type2bit(::Type{T})\n\nThe inverse of bit2type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"docstrings/#TerrariaWiringHelper.z2number-Tuple{Bool}","page":"Docstrings","title":"TerrariaWiringHelper.z2number","text":"z2number(::Number)\nz2number(::AbstractMatrix{<:Number})\n\nConvert Number to Bool in the mathbbZ_2 sense.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> z2number(25)\ntrue\n\njulia> z2number(1:5)\n5-element BitVector:\n 1\n 0\n 1\n 0\n 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
}
